comm_cricinfo: and he strikes first ball! Perfect start for Rising Pune. Possibly an offcutter outside off, Guptill throws his hands at the ball. He flat-bats it in the air, and Tiwary leaps and takes it over his head at short cover. Good catch
comm_cricbuzz: 0.1    Unadkat to Guptill, out Caught by Manoj Tiwary!! Disastrous start from KXIP. Dream start for RPS. A gentle floater first-up from Unadkat, on a good length and well wide of off, Guptill went for the drive, can't keep it down and it's a simple catch for Tiwary - at short extra-cover. Delight amongst the crowd, despair for the KXIP supporters. Guptill c Manoj Tiwary b Unadkat 0(1)

comm_cricinfo: It's that man: Unadkat, again! He dives full-length to his left from short fine leg and takes it with both hands. Tewatia's promition has backfired. Another cross-seamer. Another one that bounces on leg stump. Cramps the batsman for room who attempts to flick but instead lobs a catch to Unadkat at 45
comm_cricbuzz: 5.2   SN Thakur to Rahul Tewatia, out Caught by Unadkat!! Unadkat is having a dream day in the field - follows up the direct hit with an acrobatic catch at short fine leg. KXIP are in doldrums now and the move to promote Tewatia up the order has failed. This was banged in short and on his body, Tewatia was late on the pull, the ball ballooned off the top-edge and lobbed behind the keeper. On another day it could have dropped down in no man's land - but not today. Unadkat moves across to his left, goes with both hands and completes a fine diving catch. Rahul Tewatia c Unadkat b SN Thakur 4(3) [4s-1]
